description: An aristocratic sighthound of ancient lineage, prized for its silky, flowing coat and elegant, aloof demeanor.

physical_traits.ears: Long, covered in silky hair, pendant
physical_traits.coat: Long, thick, silky

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, and juvenile cataracts. Their deep chest makes them susceptible to bloat.
key_health_tips: Schedule regular eye exams and thyroid checks. Feed multiple small meals to reduce bloat risk. Brush coat several times weekly to prevent matting.

description: A highly social and intelligent wild canid native to sub-Saharan Africa, known for its extraordinary cooperative hunting strategy.

physical_traits.coat: Short, sparse, mottled

health_considerations: Susceptible to distemper, rabies, and other canine diseases. Inbreeding in small wild populations raises genetic health concerns.
key_health_tips: Not a domestic breed. Conservation efforts focus on vaccination programs and habitat preservation. Not suitable as pets.

description: Known as the 'King of Terriers,' the Airedale is the largest terrier breed, combining athleticism with intelligence and a bold personality.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, wiry, with soft undercoat

health_considerations: Can be prone to hip dysplasia, skin conditions, and hypothyroidism. Eye conditions may also occur.
key_health_tips: Keep coat hand-stripped or professionally groomed. Regular exercise prevents obesity. Annual thyroid and hip evaluations are recommended.

description: A muscular, stocky terrier known for its courage, strength, and deep loyalty to its family, often misunderstood due to its powerful build.

physical_traits.coat: Short, stiff, glossy
physical_traits.tail: Short, low-set, tapering to a point

health_considerations: Susceptible to hip dysplasia, heart disease, skin allergies, and elbow dysplasia. Cerebellar ataxia can occur in some lines.
key_health_tips: Maintain healthy weight to reduce joint stress. Regular vet cardiac evaluations are advised. Allergy management through diet and dermatology checks.

description: A lively, versatile Swiss mountain dog historically used as a herding and draft dog, known for its tricolor coat and energetic spirit.

physical_traits.coat: Thick, short, double coat with tricolor pattern

health_considerations: Generally healthy but may experience hip dysplasia. Eye problems and hereditary conditions in the breed line should be monitored.
key_health_tips: Provide ample daily exercise to satisfy this working dog's energy needs. Routine hip and eye screenings are recommended.

description: The Aspin (Asong Pinoy) is the native mixed-breed dog of the Philippines, known for its resilience, adaptability, and loyal nature.

physical_traits.coat: Short to medium, dense, various colors

health_considerations: Generally hardy due to natural selection. May still be susceptible to heartworm, tick-borne diseases, and parvovirus common in tropical climates.
key_health_tips: Keep up-to-date on core vaccines and anti-parasite treatments. Regular tick and heartworm prevention is essential in tropical environments.

description: One of the smallest working terriers, the Australian Terrier is spirited and self-confident with a weather-resistant coat suited to tough terrain.

physical_traits.coat: Rough, straight outer coat with soft undercoat

health_considerations: May develop diabetes mellitus, patellar luxation, and Legg-Calvé-Perthes disease. Thyroid issues have also been noted.
key_health_tips: Monitor blood sugar levels if the dog shows unusual thirst or weight changes. Knee check-ups and annual wellness exams are important.

description: A graceful, lamb-like terrier with a distinctive pear-shaped head and crisp curly coat, possessing surprising speed and tenacity beneath its gentle appearance.

physical_traits.ears: Low-set, pendant, with silky tassel at tip
physical_traits.coat: Crisp, curly mix of hard and soft

health_considerations: Prone to Bedlington terrier copper toxicosis, a hereditary liver disease. Also at risk for PRA and renal disease.
key_health_tips: DNA test for copper toxicosis before breeding. Annual liver function tests are strongly advised. Monitor diet for copper-rich foods.

description: A gentle giant from the Swiss Alps, the Bernese Mountain Dog is known for its striking tricolor coat, calm temperament, and deep devotion to family.

physical_traits.coat: Thick, moderately long, slightly wavy tricolor
physical_traits.tail: Bushy, long, carried low when relaxed

health_considerations: Unfortunately prone to cancer, especially histiocytic sarcoma and mast cell tumors. Also susceptible to hip and elbow dysplasia and bloat.
key_health_tips: Early cancer screening is important. Feed multiple small meals to reduce bloat risk. Regular orthopedic evaluations and weight management are essential.

description: A variety of the Cavalier King Charles Spaniel with a rich chestnut and white coat, this elegant toy spaniel is affectionate and adaptable.

physical_traits.coat: Long, silky, chestnut and white

health_considerations: Prone to mitral valve disease (MVD), syringomyelia, hip dysplasia, and eye conditions. MVD is a leading cause of early death.
key_health_tips: Annual cardiac evaluations from age 1. MRI screening for syringomyelia recommended in breeding dogs. Eye exams every year.

description: Widely regarded as the world's most intelligent dog breed, the Border Collie is an intense, hardworking herding dog with boundless energy and focus.

physical_traits.coat: Rough or smooth, double coat
physical_traits.tail: Moderately long, low-set, curved at tip

health_considerations: Prone to Collie Eye Anomaly (CEA), hip dysplasia, epilepsy, and MDR1 gene drug sensitivity. Neuronal ceroid lipofuscinosis (NCL) can also occur.
key_health_tips: DNA test for CEA and MDR1 before use in breeding. Provide extensive daily mental and physical stimulation to prevent behavioral issues.

description: A no-frills working terrier from the Anglo-Scottish border, built for stamina and agility, with a distinctive otter-like head and wiry coat.

physical_traits.coat: Wiry, dense outer coat with close undercoat
physical_traits.tail: Moderately short, thick at base, carried high but not curved

health_considerations: Generally healthy. May experience hip dysplasia, heart defects, and Canine Epileptoid Cramping Syndrome (CECS or 'Spike's disease').
key_health_tips: Monitor for unusual cramping episodes that may indicate CECS. A gluten-free diet may help manage CECS. Regular cardiac checks are advised.

description: The 'American Gentleman,' the Boston Terrier is a compact, well-mannered companion with a tuxedo-like coat and lively, friendly personality.

physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, tuxedo patterned
physical_traits.tail: Short, low-set, either straight or screw

health_considerations: Brachycephalic anatomy leads to respiratory issues. Also prone to cataracts, patellar luxation, deafness, and epilepsy.
key_health_tips: Avoid overexertion in heat. Have BAOS evaluated if breathing appears labored. Regular ophthalmology checks due to prominent eyes.

description: A rugged, powerful herding and working dog from Belgium with a thick, rough coat and calm, intelligent disposition ideal for police and military roles.

physical_traits.snout: Broad, well-developed, with beard and mustache
physical_traits.coat: Rough, thick, harsh outer coat with dense undercoat

health_considerations: Susceptible to hip dysplasia, elbow dysplasia, hypothyroidism, and eye conditions including progressive retinal atrophy.
key_health_tips: Regular joint screenings and weight management are essential for this large breed. Provide structured exercise and mental challenges daily.

description: The smooth-coated variety of the Brussels Griffon, the Brabancon is a charming, monkey-faced companion with a bold personality far exceeding its tiny size.

physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, no beard

health_considerations: Brachycephalic breed prone to breathing difficulties, syringomyelia, eye issues, and patellar luxation.
key_health_tips: Avoid excessive heat. Screen for syringomyelia in breeding dogs. Regular eye and respiratory evaluations are recommended.

description: An energetic and versatile gun dog from France, the Brittany is known for its hunting prowess, biddable nature, and compact, athletic build.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, flat or wavy, orange and white or liver and white

health_considerations: May develop hip dysplasia, epilepsy, and hypothyroidism. Ear infections can occur due to floppy ears.
key_health_tips: Clean ears regularly to prevent infections. Provide vigorous daily exercise. Annual thyroid and hip screenings are beneficial.

description: The older and larger of the two Corgi breeds, the Cardigan Welsh Corgi is a sturdy, long-bodied herding dog with a full tail and fox-like expression.

physical_traits.ears: Large, prominent, erect with slightly rounded tips
physical_traits.coat: Medium-length, dense, hard-textured double coat

health_considerations: Prone to intervertebral disc disease (IVDD) due to long spine, progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), and hip dysplasia.
key_health_tips: Minimize jumping on and off furniture to protect the spine. Eye exams annually. Maintain healthy weight to reduce back strain.

description: A powerful, hardworking American retriever bred to hunt waterfowl in the cold, rough waters of the Chesapeake Bay, with a distinctive wavy, oily coat.

physical_traits.coat: Short, wavy, oily, water-resistant

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, and exercise-induced collapse (EIC).
key_health_tips: DNA test for EIC and PRA. Routine joint evaluations due to active lifestyle. Annual eye exams recommended.

description: The world's smallest dog breed, the Chihuahua is a bold and loyal companion with a larger-than-life personality packed into a tiny frame.

physical_traits.ears: Large, erect, flaring to sides at a 45-degree angle
physical_traits.coat: Smooth or long, soft
physical_traits.tail: Medium-length, carried high, sickle-shaped or curled

health_considerations: Vulnerable to hypoglycemia, patellar luxation, heart disease, and hydrocephalus. Prone to dental overcrowding.
key_health_tips: Feed small, frequent meals to prevent hypoglycemia. Regular dental cleanings are critical. Protect from cold due to small body mass.

description: A distinctive terrier with a long, low body and a large, domed head topped with a silky topknot, originally bred to hunt otters and badgers.

physical_traits.coat: Crisp mixture of hard and soft hair

health_considerations: Prone to intervertebral disc disease due to elongated spine, glaucoma, and Cushing's disease.
key_health_tips: Limit jumping to protect the spinal discs. Routine eye pressure checks due to glaucoma risk. Regular vet checkups for hormonal issues.

description: A sleek, powerful, and highly intelligent breed originally developed as a guard dog in Germany, known for its loyalty and versatility in working roles.

physical_traits.snout: Long, strong, parallel to top of skull
physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, hard
physical_traits.tail: Docked short traditionally, or long and natural

health_considerations: Prone to dilated cardiomyopathy (DCM), von Willebrand's disease, hip dysplasia, and Wobbler syndrome.
key_health_tips: Annual cardiac screenings with echocardiogram. DNA test for vWD. Monitor for neck and limb coordination issues indicating Wobbler syndrome.

description: One of the oldest dog breeds, the English Foxhound is a pack hunter bred for stamina and scenting ability, with a harmonious and sociable nature.

physical_traits.ears: Pendant, rounded at tip, set low
physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, glossy

health_considerations: Generally healthy. May develop hip dysplasia and renal disease. Epilepsy has been noted in some bloodlines.
key_health_tips: Provide vigorous daily exercise; bored foxhounds can be destructive. Annual hip evaluations and kidney function tests recommended.

description: A beautiful, elegant gun dog with a silky, speckled coat known as 'belton,' valued for its gentle temperament, grace, and keen bird-hunting ability.

physical_traits.coat: Long, silky, flat, feathered, belton pattern

health_considerations: Susceptible to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, deafness (especially in lightly pigmented dogs), and allergies.
key_health_tips: BAER test for deafness in puppies. Annual thyroid and hip evaluations. Regular grooming prevents mat formation in feathered coat.

description: A cheerful, versatile gun dog known for its enthusiasm and ability to 'spring' game from cover, equally at home in the field and as a devoted companion.

physical_traits.ears: Long, pendant, close to cheeks, feathered
physical_traits.coat: Moderately long, dense, flat or wavy

health_considerations: Can suffer from hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), and Springer rage syndrome (sudden aggression, a temperament disorder).
key_health_tips: Seek reputable breeders to avoid rage syndrome lines. Regular eye and hip evaluations. Clean ears weekly to prevent infection.

description: The smallest of the four Swiss mountain dogs, the Entlebucher is a compact, agile herder with a tricolor coat and a loyal, energetic personality.

physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, harsh, tricolor

health_considerations: May be affected by hip dysplasia and progressive retinal atrophy. Ectopic ureters have also been documented in the breed.
key_health_tips: DNA and OFA testing for PRA and hip health before breeding. Provide daily vigorous activity to manage high energy levels.

description: A powerful Nordic sled dog developed by the indigenous peoples of the Arctic, bred for endurance hauling in extreme cold-weather conditions.

physical_traits.coat: Dense double coat, thick undercoat, weather-resistant

health_considerations: Generally robust. May experience hip dysplasia and inherited eye disorders. Bloat is a concern given their deep chest.
key_health_tips: Feed multiple small meals to prevent bloat. Regular exercise is essential. Annual eye and hip evaluations recommended.

description: A compact, bat-eared charmer with a playful, adaptable nature, the French Bulldog has become one of the most popular breeds worldwide.

physical_traits.ears: Large, bat-like, erect, rounded at top
physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, fine

health_considerations: Brachycephalic Obstructive Airway Syndrome (BOAS) is a major concern. Also prone to spinal issues, skin fold dermatitis, and heat sensitivity.
key_health_tips: Avoid overexertion and heat. Clean skin folds regularly. BOAS surgical evaluation may be necessary. Avoid air travel in cargo when possible.

description: One of the world's most versatile and beloved working breeds, known for its intelligence, loyalty, and capability across police, military, and service roles.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, double coat, medium or long
physical_traits.tail: Long, bushy, hanging in a slight curve

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, degenerative myelopathy, bloat, and perianal fistulas. Skin and digestive issues also common.
key_health_tips: OFA screening for joints before breeding. Degenerative myelopathy DNA testing available. Feed multiple small meals to prevent bloat.

description: An all-purpose gundog of noble bearing, the GSP is an enthusiastic hunter on land and water with a sleek liver or liver-roan coat and boundless stamina.

physical_traits.coat: Short, thick, water-resistant, liver/liver-roan
physical_traits.tail: Docked to 40% in some regions, or natural

health_considerations: Can suffer from hip dysplasia, bloat, heart disease, and cone degeneration (a hereditary eye disorder).
key_health_tips: DNA test for cone degeneration. Use slow-feed bowls and structured meals to reduce bloat risk. Provide 2+ hours of exercise daily.

description: The heaviest of the setter breeds, Scotland's Gordon Setter is a dignified, loyal bird dog with a striking black-and-tan coat and steadfast character.

physical_traits.snout: Long, not pointed, slightly broader at top
physical_traits.coat: Soft, silky, slightly wavy, black with rich tan markings
physical_traits.tail: Straight or slightly curved, carried horizontally

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, and hypothyroidism. Bloat also possible due to deep chest.
key_health_tips: Eye and thyroid exams annually. OFA hip testing recommended. Feed controlled meals with rest after eating to prevent bloat.

description: Known as the 'Apollo of Dogs,' the Great Dane is a gentle giant with a regal, powerful build and a friendly, patient temperament.

physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, smooth
physical_traits.tail: Long, tapering to tip, carried level or slightly curved

health_considerations: Highly susceptible to bloat/GDV (life-threatening), dilated cardiomyopathy, hip dysplasia, and wobbler syndrome.
key_health_tips: Preventive gastropexy surgery is often recommended. Cardiac evaluations annually. Avoid vigorous exercise immediately before or after meals.

description: A majestic flock guardian from the Pyrenean mountains, the Great Pyrenees is a calm, patient dog with a brilliant white coat built for harsh conditions.

physical_traits.coat: Thick double coat, weather-resistant, white
physical_traits.tail: Long, plume-like, curled over back when alert

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, bloat, osteosarcoma, and patellar luxation. Addison's disease has also been noted.
key_health_tips: Regular joint and cardiac screenings. Prevent bloat with meal scheduling. Keep weight in check as extra pounds stress joints significantly.

description: The largest of the Swiss mountain dogs, the Greater Swiss is a draft and herding dog with a bold tricolor coat, friendly nature, and impressive strength.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, medium-length, tricolor

health_considerations: Subject to hip and elbow dysplasia, bloat, epilepsy, and urinary incontinence especially in females.
key_health_tips: Joint screening before breeding. Manage meal portions and timing to reduce bloat risk. Spay timing can help reduce incontinence in females.

description: An elegant, deer-like sighthound from the Balearic Islands, the Ibizan Hound hunts by sight, sound, and scent with remarkable agility.

physical_traits.coat: Smooth or wire-haired, short to medium

health_considerations: Generally healthy. May develop seizures, allergies, and axonal dystrophy (a rare hereditary neurological disorder).
key_health_tips: Keep up with vaccinations as the breed can have sensitivities. Secure fencing required as they are exceptional jumpers. Monitor for allergic reactions.

description: A rollicking, high-spirited gun dog with a rich mahogany coat, known for its outgoing nature, speed in the field, and love of people.

physical_traits.coat: Silky, straight, rich mahogany

health_considerations: Susceptible to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), and bloat. Celiac-like gluten sensitivity has also been found.
key_health_tips: DNA test for PRA. Consider gluten-free diet if digestive issues arise. Active exercise required daily. Feed multiple small meals.

description: One of the oldest terrier breeds, the Irish Terrier is a bold, fiery companion with a distinctive red wiry coat and fearless, devoted character.

physical_traits.snout: Long, strong, well-filled before the eyes
physical_traits.ears: Small, V-shaped, folded forward close to cheeks
physical_traits.coat: Dense, wiry, straight, red/golden red

health_considerations: A largely healthy breed. Possible issues include urinary bladder stones, hyperkeratosis of footpads, and muscular dystrophy in some lines.
key_health_tips: Monitor paw pads for thickening or cracking. Annual wellness checks. Provide mental and physical challenges to satisfy this spirited breed.

description: The tallest of the spaniels, this curly-coated, liver-colored water dog is an enthusiastic swimmer and tireless retriever with a whimsical topknot.

physical_traits.ears: Very long, pendant, covered in dense curls
physical_traits.coat: Tight, crisp ringlets over body, smooth rat-like tail
physical_traits.tail: Short, thick at base, smooth, tapers to a fine point

health_considerations: Susceptible to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, and vaccine sensitivity reactions. Ear infections common due to floppy, hairy ears.
key_health_tips: Clean and dry ears thoroughly after swimming. Discuss vaccine protocols with vet given sensitivities. Annual thyroid checks advised.

description: The tallest of all dog breeds, the Irish Wolfhound is an ancient sighthound of commanding presence with a calm, dignified, and gentle spirit.

physical_traits.ears: Small, pendant, close to face, rose-shaped
physical_traits.coat: Rough, hard, wiry

health_considerations: Prone to dilated cardiomyopathy, osteosarcoma, bloat, and hip dysplasia. The breed has one of the shortest lifespans among dogs.
key_health_tips: Annual cardiac screening critical. Elevate food bowls and use slow feeders. Preventive gastropexy is often recommended at spay/neuter time.

description: A miniature sighthound of ancient lineage, the Italian Greyhound is elegant, affectionate, and devoted, combining grace with surprising speed.

physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, satin-like

health_considerations: Delicate bone structure makes fractures common. Also prone to dental disease, progressive retinal atrophy, and epilepsy.
key_health_tips: Avoid rough play or jumping from heights. Brush teeth daily. Annual eye exams. Keep warm as they have very little body fat and no undercoat.

description: Also known as the Japanese Chin, this aristocratic toy breed is known for its cat-like behavior, butterfly-wing ears, and flowing silky coat.

physical_traits.coat: Silky, profuse, straight, fine

health_considerations: Prone to brachycephalic issues, heart disease, cataracts, and heat sensitivity. May experience episodes of spinning or fly-catching (GM2 gangliosidosis).
key_health_tips: Avoid heat and strenuous exercise. Annual cardiac and eye checks. Screen breeding dogs for GM2 gangliosidosis, a rare but fatal neurological condition.

description: Ireland's national dog, the Kerry Blue Terrier is a versatile working terrier with a unique blue-gray coat and a spirited, people-loving personality.

physical_traits.coat: Soft, dense, wavy, blue-gray

health_considerations: Prone to progressive neuronal abiotrophy (PNA, a movement disorder), hip dysplasia, and certain cancers.
key_health_tips: DNA test available for PNA. Annual orthopedic evaluations. Grooming is required every 6-8 weeks to maintain coat texture and cleanliness.

description: America's most popular dog breed for decades, the Labrador is a friendly, outgoing retriever equally skilled as a hunting companion, service dog, and family pet.

physical_traits.ears: Pendant, moderate-sized, hanging close to head
physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, hard, weather-resistant double coat
physical_traits.tail: Thick at base, tapers to tip, covered with dense fur, 'otter tail'

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, obesity, exercise-induced collapse (EIC), and progressive retinal atrophy. Obesity significantly worsens joint problems.
key_health_tips: Carefully manage food intake; Labs are notorious overeaters. OFA and EIC testing recommended. Regular exercise maintains weight and joint health.

description: A compact, spirited terrier from England's Lake District, originally bred to hunt foxes from rocky terrain, now a lively show and companion dog.

physical_traits.ears: Small, V-shaped, folded slightly to the side
physical_traits.coat: Thick, wiry outer coat with dense undercoat

health_considerations: Relatively healthy. May experience Legg-Calvé-Perthes disease and lens luxation.
key_health_tips: Annual eye examinations to monitor for lens luxation. Hand-stripping the coat preserves its proper texture. Adequate daily exercise prevents boredom.

description: A majestic giant bred to resemble the lion in the town crest of Leonberg, Germany, with a lion-like mane and gentle, family-oriented nature.

physical_traits.coat: Long, lion-yellow, water-resistant, with black mane on neck/chest
physical_traits.tail: Well-feathered, long, carried level or slightly curved

health_considerations: Susceptible to Leonberger Polyneuropathy (LPN, a hereditary neuromuscular condition), hip dysplasia, osteosarcoma, and heart disease.
key_health_tips: DNA test for LPN variants before breeding. Cardiac and orthopedic evaluations annually. Monitor gait for early signs of nerve involvement.

description: An ancient sentinel dog from Tibet's Himalayan monasteries, the Lhasa Apso is watchful, independent, and cloaked in a floor-length flowing coat.

physical_traits.coat: Long, straight, dense, floor-length in all colors

health_considerations: Prone to hereditary kidney disease (renal cortical hypoplasia), patellar luxation, hip dysplasia, and eye conditions.
key_health_tips: Kidney function screening important in breeding lines. Annual ophthalmology exams. Daily coat brushing prevents painful matting.

description: One of the oldest toy breeds, the Maltese is a charming, lively companion draped in a long white silky coat, bred solely for the purpose of companionship.

physical_traits.coat: Straight, long, silky, pure white

health_considerations: Prone to hypoglycemia, dental disease, luxating patella, liver shunts, and progressive retinal atrophy.
key_health_tips: Feed small frequent meals to prevent hypoglycemia. Dental exams at least annually. Tear stain management with regular facial cleaning.

description: One of the world's oldest and rarest breeds, the Xoloitzcuintli (Xolo) is an ancient Mexican dog prized for its calm demeanor and unique hairless body.

physical_traits.coat: Hairless (or coated variety with short fur)
physical_traits.tail: Long, thin, tapers to fine point

health_considerations: Hairless skin requires sun protection and moisturizing. May be missing some premolar teeth. Generally a very robust and long-lived breed.
key_health_tips: Apply pet-safe sunscreen on outdoor excursions. Moisturize exposed skin regularly. Dental checks are important due to possible tooth absence.

description: A massive, sweet-tempered water rescue dog from Canada, the Newfoundland is known as a 'nanny dog' for its remarkable patience and gentleness with children.

physical_traits.ears: Small, triangular, pendant, close to head
physical_traits.coat: Flat, dense, water-resistant double coat, black or brown
physical_traits.tail: Broad, strong, carried low in repose, horizontal when moving

health_considerations: Prone to subvalvular aortic stenosis (SAS), hip dysplasia, cystinuria (bladder stones), and bloat.
key_health_tips: Cardiac evaluation at every wellness check; SAS can be fatal if undetected. DNA test for cystinuria. Keep weight controlled to protect joints.

description: The smallest of the working terriers, the Norfolk is a lovable, sociable dog with drop ears, a wiry coat, and big-hearted fearlessness.

physical_traits.ears: Small, V-shaped, drop ears, folded forward
physical_traits.coat: Wiry, hard, straight, close-lying

health_considerations: Generally healthy. Mitral valve disease has been noted at higher rates. May also develop hip dysplasia and upper airway syndrome.
key_health_tips: Annual cardiac evaluations from age 5. Routine dental care. Strip coat rather than clip to preserve texture.

description: An ancient Nordic spitz breed used to hunt elk and bear, the Norwegian Elkhound is bold, loyal, and energetic with a distinctive thick gray coat.

physical_traits.coat: Thick, hard, dense outer coat with soft undercoat, gray

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), Fanconi syndrome (kidney disease), and obesity.
key_health_tips: DNA test for PRA. Kidney function monitoring especially in older dogs. Limit treats; this breed is prone to weight gain. Provide vigorous daily exercise.

description: One of the smallest terrier breeds, the Norwich Terrier features erect ears, a wiry coat, and a devoted, fearless personality with a big-dog spirit.

physical_traits.coat: Straight, wiry, hard, lying close to body

health_considerations: Prone to upper airway syndrome, mitral valve disease, and epilepsy. Hip dysplasia is possible.
key_health_tips: Screen for upper airway abnormalities if breathing sounds labored. Annual cardiac checks. Coat requires hand-stripping for proper texture.

description: An iconic, shaggy herding dog with a bear-like shuffle and a warm, adaptable temperament, recognized worldwide by its fluffy, profuse coat.

physical_traits.coat: Long, profuse, shaggy, hard-textured double coat

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, autoimmune conditions, and deafness. Extensive coat care is a health consideration itself.
key_health_tips: Brush coat multiple times weekly to prevent painful matting and skin infections. Annual eye and hearing checks. OFA hip testing recommended.

description: An ancient imperial Chinese breed of regal dignity, the Pekingese carries itself with an air of self-importance and is devoted to its chosen person.

physical_traits.coat: Long, coarse outer coat with thick undercoat, double mane

health_considerations: Brachycephalic issues including breathing difficulty and eye exposure injuries. Also prone to intervertebral disc disease, heart problems, and skin fold infections.
key_health_tips: Clean facial folds daily. Avoid heat and overexertion. Use a harness rather than a collar to minimize throat pressure. Regular eye and cardiac exams.

description: The Queen's favorite dog, the Pembroke Welsh Corgi is a lively, affectionate herding dog with a fox-like face, expressive eyes, and naturally short tail.

physical_traits.ears: Firm, erect, medium-sized, rounded at tips
physical_traits.coat: Medium-length, dense, double coat, red, sable, or tricolor

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, degenerative myelopathy (DM), progressive retinal atrophy, and intervertebral disc disease (IVDD).
key_health_tips: DNA test for DM and PRA. Use ramps and minimize stairs to protect spine. Annual orthopedic and eye evaluations.

description: A bold, vivacious toy dog with a fox-like face and an immense, fluffy double coat descended from large Nordic sled dogs, now a beloved companion.

physical_traits.coat: Profuse double coat, thick undercoat, straight outer coat

health_considerations: Prone to patellar luxation, heart disease, alopecia X (black skin disease), tracheal collapse, and hypoglycemia in puppies.
key_health_tips: Use a harness to prevent tracheal collapse. Avoid rough play or falls. Annual cardiac and orthopedic checks. Feed frequent small meals in young dogs.

description: A powerful, dignified African hound originally bred to track lions, recognized by the distinctive ridge of reversed hair along its back.

physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, sleek, wheaten to red wheaten

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, dermoid sinus (a congenital skin defect along the ridge), hypothyroidism, and elbow dysplasia.
key_health_tips: Check puppies for dermoid sinus early. Annual thyroid and joint screenings. Early socialization and obedience training are essential for this powerful breed.

description: A robust, powerful working dog of German origin used historically as a herder and draft dog, now a popular guardian, police dog, and loyal companion.

physical_traits.snout: Broad, deep, muzzle and skull equally long
physical_traits.ears: Medium, pendant, triangular, close to head
physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, coarse outer with undercoat

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, osteosarcoma, dilated cardiomyopathy, and aortic stenosis.
key_health_tips: Annual cardiac and orthopedic evaluations. Cancer vigilance is important given breed predisposition. Early socialization and consistent training are critical.

description: A legendary Alpine rescue dog from the Swiss hospice, the Saint Bernard is massive, warm-hearted, and gentle, famous for saving travelers in mountain passes.

physical_traits.coat: Short and rough (smooth) or long and rough, orange, red-brindle, brownish-yellow with white
physical_traits.tail: Long, heavy, hanging low with slight upward curve

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, bloat, osteosarcoma, dilated cardiomyopathy, and eye issues like ectropion.
key_health_tips: Preventive gastropexy for bloat. Annual cardiac and joint screenings. Manage growth rate in puppies to reduce orthopedic disease risk.

description: One of the oldest known dog breeds, the Saluki is a swift, graceful sighthound revered in the Middle East, combining breathtaking speed with gentle devotion.

physical_traits.ears: Long, covered with long silky hair, mobile
physical_traits.coat: Smooth and silky, feathered on ears and tail

health_considerations: Prone to cardiac conditions, hemangiosarcoma, and hypothyroidism. Very thin skin and low body fat make them sensitive to anesthesia.
key_health_tips: Notify vet of sighthound anesthesia sensitivity before any procedure. Annual cardiac and thyroid exams. Provide secure fencing as they can run at high speed.

description: A beautiful, smiling spitz from Siberia, the Samoyed is a friendly, gentle herding and sled dog with a brilliant white double coat and perpetually happy expression.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, straight, white or cream double coat with heavy undercoat
physical_traits.tail: Long, well-feathered, carried curled over back

health_considerations: Prone to Samoyed Hereditary Glomerulopathy (a kidney disorder), hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, and diabetes mellitus.
key_health_tips: DNA test for hereditary glomerulopathy in breeding dogs. Annual kidney and eye screenings. Extensive daily grooming prevents matting and skin issues.

description: The dignified and feisty Scottish Terrier is an independent, spirited dog with a wiry coat and distinctive beard, affectionately known as the 'Diehard.'

physical_traits.snout: Long, slightly convex, with full beard
physical_traits.ears: Small, erect, pointed, covered with velvety hair
physical_traits.coat: Dense, hard, wiry outer coat with soft undercoat
physical_traits.tail: Short, thick at base, carried erect

health_considerations: Prone to Scottie cramp (a movement disorder), von Willebrand's disease, bladder cancer, and craniomandibular osteopathy in puppies.
key_health_tips: DNA test for vWD. Annual wellness checks for early cancer detection. Avoid high-stress situations that may trigger Scottie cramp episodes.

description: A noble, gentle giant from the Scottish Highlands, the Deerhound was bred to course red deer and is now a calm, dignified companion with a rough, gray coat.

physical_traits.coat: Rough, wiry, ragged, blue-gray

health_considerations: Prone to bloat, cardiomyopathy, osteosarcoma, and cystinuria. Sighthound sensitivity to anesthesia must be flagged to vets.
key_health_tips: Preventive gastropexy may be advised. Cardiac screenings annually. Notify veterinarians of sighthound anesthesia requirements before any surgery.

description: A rare and charming Welsh terrier developed for otter and badger hunting, the Sealyham is low-slung with a distinctive long white coat and outgoing personality.

physical_traits.snout: Long, broad, square, with full beard
physical_traits.ears: Pendant, level with top of head, folded forward
physical_traits.coat: Dense, wiry outer coat, soft undercoat, white

health_considerations: May develop lens luxation, hereditary deafness, and retinal dysplasia. Generally healthier than many other terrier breeds.
key_health_tips: BAER testing for deafness in puppies. Annual eye exams. Maintain grooming routine as coat requires stripping or trimming every few months.

description: Often called the Sheltie, this smaller version of the Rough Collie is highly intelligent, vocal, and devoted, excelling in herding, agility, and obedience.

physical_traits.ears: Small, semi-erect, folding forward at tip
physical_traits.coat: Long, rough outer coat with dense undercoat

health_considerations: Susceptible to Collie Eye Anomaly (CEA), MDR1 mutation, hip dysplasia, dermatomyositis, and von Willebrand's disease.
key_health_tips: DNA testing for CEA and MDR1 mandatory before breeding. Inform vet of MDR1 status before any medication or procedure. Annual eye exams important.

description: A small but robust 'lion dog' from ancient China, the Shih Tzu is a sweet-tempered, affectionate companion with a luxurious flowing coat and pushed-in face.

physical_traits.ears: Large, pendant, covered with long hair
physical_traits.coat: Long, flowing, dense double coat in all colors

health_considerations: Prone to brachycephalic airway issues, intervertebral disc disease, renal dysplasia, eye proptosis, and hip dysplasia.
key_health_tips: Keep eyes clean daily to prevent staining and corneal injuries. Avoid heat and overexertion. Use harness not collar. Regular dental cleanings are needed.

description: A striking, wolf-like sled dog from northeastern Siberia, the Siberian Husky is a free-spirited, mischievous, and highly energetic working breed.

physical_traits.coat: Dense double coat, medium-length, all colors
physical_traits.tail: Moderately bushy, carried in a sickle curve

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, hereditary eye conditions (juvenile cataracts, corneal dystrophy, PRA), and hypothyroidism.
key_health_tips: Annual CERF eye exams. DNA test for hereditary eye diseases. Provide vigorous daily exercise to prevent destructive behavior. Secure fencing is essential.

description: A muscular, affectionate British breed known as the 'nanny dog' for its remarkable patience and love of children, combined with tenacity and courage.

physical_traits.coat: Smooth, short, close-fitting
physical_traits.tail: Medium-length, low-set, tapering to a point

health_considerations: Susceptible to hereditary juvenile cataracts, hip dysplasia, L-2-hydroxyglutaric aciduria (a metabolic disorder), and skin allergies.
key_health_tips: DNA test for hereditary cataracts and L2HGA before breeding. Annual eye and joint evaluations. Management of skin allergies through diet and dermatology.

description: A rare, heavy-bodied English spaniel with a rich golden-liver coat, known for its slow but persistent hunting style and gentle, calm nature.

physical_traits.ears: Large, thick, pendant, set moderately low
physical_traits.coat: Flat, rich golden-liver, well-feathered
physical_traits.tail: Docked or natural, feathered, carried low

health_considerations: Prone to intervertebral disc disease, pulmonic stenosis (a heart defect), hip and elbow dysplasia, and ear infections.
key_health_tips: Routine cardiac evaluations especially for young dogs. Keep ears clean and dry. Limit high-impact jumping to protect the spine.

description: One of the largest and most ancient breeds, the Tibetan Mastiff is a formidable flock and property guardian from the Himalayas with a lion-like mane.

physical_traits.coat: Thick double coat, profuse mane on neck, all colors

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, inherited epilepsy, and osteochondrosis. Bloat possible due to large, deep chest.
key_health_tips: Thyroid testing recommended annually. Orthopedic and neurological evaluations for breeding dogs. Early socialization is critical for this powerful guardian.

description: Despite the name, the Tibetan Terrier is not a true terrier but a lucky charm dog from Tibetan monasteries, with a shaggy coat and large flat snowshoe-like feet.

physical_traits.coat: Double coat, fine woolly undercoat, long wavy outer coat
physical_traits.tail: Medium-length, well-feathered, carried curled over back

health_considerations: Prone to progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), lens luxation, hip dysplasia, and neuronal ceroid lipofuscinosis (NCL).
key_health_tips: DNA tests for PRA and NCL are available. Annual eye and joint evaluations. Coat requires regular brushing to prevent matting.

description: An American scenthound developed in Kentucky for hunting raccoon and deer, the Treeing Walker Coonhound is fast, confident, and vocal on the trail.

physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, glossy, tricolor
physical_traits.tail: Medium-length, carried upright like a saber

health_considerations: Generally healthy. May experience hip dysplasia and ear infections due to long pendant ears.
key_health_tips: Clean ears weekly to prevent infections. Provide vigorous daily exercise. Secure fencing is vital as scent trails can lead them away quickly.

description: The 'Gray Ghost,' the Weimaraner is a sleek, aristocratic German gun dog with striking silver-gray coat and amber or blue eyes, bred for all-purpose hunting.

physical_traits.ears: Long, pendant, rounded at tip, high-set
physical_traits.coat: Short, sleek, silver-gray

health_considerations: Highly susceptible to bloat/GDV. Also prone to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, and von Willebrand's disease.
key_health_tips: Preventive gastropexy surgery often recommended. Use slow feeders and avoid exercise around mealtimes. Annual thyroid and joint screenings.

description: A loyal, active, and affectionate gun dog from Wales, the Welsh Springer Spaniel has a distinctive rich red and white coat and a tireless work ethic.

physical_traits.ears: Pendant, set at eye level, narrow and tapered
physical_traits.coat: Flat, dense, silky, red and white

health_considerations: May develop hip dysplasia, glaucoma, and epilepsy. Ear infections are common due to the pendant ear structure.
key_health_tips: Glaucoma eye pressure checks annually. Clean ears after water exposure. Provide vigorous daily exercise for this energetic sporting breed.

description: The cheerful 'Westie' is a confident, self-assured terrier with a striking all-white coat, known for its outgoing and entertaining personality.

physical_traits.coat: Straight, hard outer coat with short soft undercoat, white

health_considerations: Prone to Westie Lung Disease (idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis), skin conditions (Westie armadillo syndrome), craniomandibular osteopathy, and hip dysplasia.
key_health_tips: Monitor breathing patterns for early lung disease signs. Manage skin with regular baths and appropriate diet. Annual X-rays may help detect hip issues.

description: A feisty, bold toy terrier with a glamorous steel-blue and golden-tan silky coat, the Yorkie packs enormous personality into a tiny, elegant package.

physical_traits.ears: Small, V-shaped, erect, set not too far apart
physical_traits.coat: Long, silky, fine, blue and tan
physical_traits.tail: Docked or natural, carried above level of back

health_considerations: Prone to hypoglycemia, tracheal collapse, patellar luxation, Legg-Calvé-Perthes, and dental overcrowding.
key_health_tips: Use a harness not a collar to protect the trachea. Frequent small meals to prevent hypoglycemia. Regular dental cleanings are essential.

description: A small, confident terrier-like companion with a monkey-like face and spirited personality, the Affenpinscher (meaning 'monkey terrier') is full of character.

physical_traits.coat: Rough, wiry

health_considerations: Generally sturdy but can suffer from patellar luxation and dental issues due to small jaws. Regular dental care and monitoring for joint problems are important.
key_health_tips: Brush teeth several times per week to avoid periodontal disease. Monitor for signs of knee instability and keep a healthy weight to reduce joint stress.

description: An ancient African hunting dog known as the 'barkless dog,' the Basenji communicates with an unusual yodel-like sound and is cat-like in its cleanliness and independence.

physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, fine

health_considerations: Prone to Fanconi syndrome (a kidney disorder), progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), hypothyroidism, and hip dysplasia.
key_health_tips: Annual urine amino acid tests to screen for Fanconi syndrome. DNA test for PRA. Secure fencing essential as Basenjis are skilled escape artists.

description: A low-slung, large-boned scenthound with drooping ears and soulful eyes, the Basset Hound is calm, friendly, and possesses an extraordinary sense of smell.

physical_traits.ears: Very long, velvety, low-set, curling inward
physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, hard-textured, tricolor or bicolor
physical_traits.tail: Long, tapering, carried high with slight curve

health_considerations: Prone to bloat, hip and elbow dysplasia, obesity, ear infections, and intervertebral disc disease due to elongated spine.
key_health_tips: Clean ears weekly; the long drooping ears trap moisture and debris. Feed controlled portions to prevent obesity. Multiple small meals help reduce bloat risk.

description: A merry, curious, and compact scenthound with a big personality and an even bigger nose, the Beagle is one of the most popular breeds in the world.

physical_traits.ears: Long, broad, pendant, rounded at tips
physical_traits.coat: Dense, hard, close, tricolor or bicolor

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, epilepsy, progressive retinal atrophy, and obesity.
key_health_tips: Monitor calorie intake strictly; Beagles are notorious for overeating. Annual thyroid and eye screenings. Keep on leash or in secure yard due to nose-driven wandering.

description: A powerful, determined American scenthound developed to trail and tree raccoon, the Black and Tan Coonhound has a deep voice and a tireless work ethic.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, short, glossy, black with rich tan markings

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, ear infections, bloat, and obesity.
key_health_tips: Clean ears weekly to prevent infections. Feed controlled amounts and avoid rapid exercise after meals to reduce bloat risk.

description: The world's finest tracking dog, the Bloodhound's nose can follow scent trails days old, and its evidence is admissible in court in the United States.

physical_traits.snout: Very long, deep, furrowed, pendulous lips
physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, hard, black and tan or red
physical_traits.tail: Long, tapering, carried upright with a slight curve

health_considerations: Prone to bloat, hip and elbow dysplasia, ear infections, eye problems (entropion/ectropion), and skin fold infections.
key_health_tips: Slow feeder bowls and two meals a day reduce bloat risk. Clean wrinkles and ears regularly. Eye and skin fold inspections at every wellness visit.

description: An American scenthound with a distinctive blue-ticked coat, known for its cold nose (ability to track old trails) and loud, bawling voice on the hunt.

physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, glossy, blue-ticked with black and tan

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, ear infections, and bloat. Generally a hardy breed but requires significant exercise.
key_health_tips: Regular ear cleaning after outdoor use. Structured mealtimes and slow feeding help prevent bloat. Provide substantial daily exercise in secure areas.

description: An elegant Russian sighthound bred by the aristocracy to course wolves across open steppes, the Borzoi is silky, graceful, and serenely independent.

physical_traits.coat: Long, silky, wavy or curly, all colors
physical_traits.tail: Long, well-feathered, low-set, slight saber curve

health_considerations: Prone to bloat, osteosarcoma, progressive retinal atrophy, and cardiac issues. Highly sensitive to anesthesia as a sighthound.
key_health_tips: Alert veterinarians to sighthound anesthesia sensitivity. Preventive gastropexy for bloat. Annual eye and cardiac evaluations. Secure fencing always required.

description: A playful, energetic, and loyal companion of German origin, the Boxer is a beloved family dog known for its squarely built body, wrinkled brow, and puppy-like enthusiasm.

physical_traits.ears: Medium, high-set, thin, naturally pendant or cropped
physical_traits.coat: Short, shiny, smooth, fawn or brindle with white markings

health_considerations: Prone to various heart conditions (aortic stenosis, cardiomyopathy), hip dysplasia, degenerative myelopathy, and a high rate of cancer including mast cell tumors.
key_health_tips: Annual cardiac evaluations are critical. Cancer awareness is important for this breed. Holter monitor testing for arrhythmias in breeding dogs.

description: An ancient French herding and war dog with a long, shaggy coat and distinctive double dew claws, known for its intelligence, loyalty, and protective nature.

physical_traits.snout: Long, broad, with mustache and beard
physical_traits.coat: Long, coarse, dry, wavy outer coat with fine undercoat
physical_traits.tail: Long, well-feathered, curling slightly at tip

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), night blindness (stationary night blindness, a hereditary condition), and bloat.
key_health_tips: DNA test for stationary night blindness in breeding dogs. Annual eye and joint evaluations. Coat requires brushing multiple times weekly.

description: A powerful, loyal guardian developed by English gamekeepers to catch poachers, the Bullmastiff combines the speed of a Bulldog with the size of a Mastiff.

physical_traits.ears: V-shaped, folded, pendant, set wide and high
physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, hard, fawn, red, or brindle

health_considerations: Susceptible to hip and elbow dysplasia, bloat, lymphoma, heart disease, and various cancers. Brachycephalic breathing issues can also occur.
key_health_tips: Cancer and cardiac monitoring throughout life. Feed twice daily with rest after meals. Maintain lean body weight to reduce joint and cardiac stress.

description: Immortalized as Toto in The Wizard of Oz, the Cairn Terrier is one of the oldest terrier breeds from Scotland, spirited, hardy, and always ready for adventure.

physical_traits.coat: Abundant, harsh, weather-resistant outer coat with soft undercoat
physical_traits.tail: Short, well-furnished with hair, carried upright

health_considerations: Prone to Legg-Calvé-Perthes disease, patellar luxation, ocular melanosis, and liver portosystemic shunts.
key_health_tips: Eye and orthopedic evaluations annually. Liver function should be checked if neurological symptoms appear. Avoid overfeeding; obesity worsens joint conditions.

description: One of the most distinctive dog breeds, the Chow Chow has a lion-like mane, scowling expression, and unique blue-black tongue, combined with a dignified, aloof personality.

physical_traits.ears: Small, thick, erect, rounded at tip
physical_traits.coat: Rough (abundant, thick, outer coat) or smooth variety
physical_traits.tail: Set high, carried closely over back

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, entropion (eye lid abnormality), hypothyroidism, and allergies. Brachycephalic tendencies can cause breathing issues.
key_health_tips: Annual eye exams for entropion. OFA joint evaluations. Thyroid testing recommended. Regular brushing prevents painful coat matting.

description: A heavy, low-slung spaniel with a dignified, placid temperament, the Clumber is the largest of the spaniels, developed for slow, methodical hunting in dense cover.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, silky, flat, white with lemon or orange markings

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, intervertebral disc disease, entropion, and exercise-induced collapse (EIC).
key_health_tips: DNA test for EIC. Eye and joint evaluations regularly. Avoid obesity which significantly stresses the long, heavy body.

description: The smallest sporting breed, the American Cocker Spaniel has the most beautiful, flowing coat of all spaniels and is a sweet-tempered, merry companion.

physical_traits.snout: Broad, deep, with full square lips
physical_traits.ears: Long, pendant, heavily feathered, set at eye level
physical_traits.coat: Silky, flat or slightly wavy, well-feathered, all colors

health_considerations: Prone to progressive retinal atrophy, cataracts, glaucoma, hip dysplasia, and immune-mediated diseases. Ear infections are very common.
key_health_tips: Clean ears weekly. Annual eye exams from puppy stage. Monitor for immune issues. Regular grooming at least every 6-8 weeks.

description: Immortalized as Lassie, the Rough Collie is a loyal, gentle herding dog from Scotland with a magnificent sable and white coat and an expressive, intelligent face.

physical_traits.coat: Abundant, rough double coat with mane and frill
physical_traits.tail: Long, carried low with upward swirl at tip

health_considerations: Prone to Collie Eye Anomaly (CEA), progressive retinal atrophy, MDR1 drug sensitivity, hip dysplasia, and dermatomyositis.
key_health_tips: DNA testing for CEA and MDR1 is essential. Annual eye exams. Inform veterinarians of MDR1 status before administering any medication.

description: One of the oldest retriever breeds, the Curly-Coated Retriever is a confident, independent water retriever covered in a mass of tight, crisp black or liver curls.

physical_traits.ears: Small, pendant, close to head, covered with curls
physical_traits.coat: Tight, crisp, water-resistant curls over body

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, glycogen storage disease (GSD), and exercise-induced collapse (EIC).
key_health_tips: DNA test for GSD and EIC. Annual eye and hip evaluations. Curly coat should not be brushed — rinse after water activities and allow to air dry.

description: An endangered wild canid native to South and Southeast Asia, the Dhole (Asiatic Wild Dog) hunts in packs and is known for its distinctive whistling call.

physical_traits.snout: Broad, slightly domed forehead, shorter than a wolf
physical_traits.coat: Thick, reddish-brown, short

health_considerations: As a wild species, susceptible to canine distemper, parvovirus, and sarcoptic mange. Habitat loss and prey depletion threaten the species.
key_health_tips: Not a domestic animal. Conservation efforts focus on protecting habitat and controlling disease transmission from domestic dogs.

description: Australia's wild dog, the Dingo is a lean, agile canid that arrived on the continent thousands of years ago, living as both a wild animal and companion to Aboriginal peoples.

physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, ginger or sandy yellow

health_considerations: Generally healthy as a wild species. Pure dingoes are threatened by hybridization with domestic dogs. Can carry heartworm and various parasites.
key_health_tips: Not suitable as conventional domestic pets. Legal restrictions apply in many Australian states. Ownership requires special permits and specialized care.

description: A perpetually youthful and exuberant gun dog, the Flat-Coated Retriever is known as the 'Peter Pan of dogs,' maintaining its puppy-like enthusiasm well into adulthood.

physical_traits.ears: Small to medium, pendant, close to head
physical_traits.coat: Dense, fine, flat-lying, black or liver

health_considerations: Unusually high rate of histiocytic sarcoma (a form of cancer). Also prone to hip dysplasia, patellar luxation, and epilepsy.
key_health_tips: Cancer vigilance throughout life; any lumps should be checked promptly. Annual orthopedic evaluations. Maintain healthy weight to reduce joint stress.

description: The largest of the three Schnauzer varieties, the Giant Schnauzer is a powerful, versatile working dog originally developed in Bavaria for cattle driving and guarding.

physical_traits.ears: Cropped erect or naturally V-shaped pendant
physical_traits.coat: Harsh, wiry, dense, with soft undercoat, pepper and salt or black

health_considerations: Prone to autoimmune thyroiditis, hip dysplasia, epilepsy, squamous cell carcinoma of the digit (toe cancer), and various autoimmune diseases.
key_health_tips: Toe inspections at every vet visit; SCC is breed-specific and often curable if caught early. Annual thyroid and orthopedic evaluations.

description: One of the most beloved breeds in the world, the Golden Retriever is a joyful, devoted, and intelligent gun dog known for its beautiful golden coat and gentle temperament.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, water-resistant double coat, golden in color
physical_traits.tail: Well-feathered, carried level or with slight upward curve

health_considerations: Has one of the highest cancer rates of any breed. Also prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, heart disease, and hypothyroidism.
key_health_tips: Annual wellness checks with cancer vigilance. OFA screening for joints. Annual eye and cardiac exams. Maintain healthy weight to protect joints.

description: The long-haired, black variety of the Belgian Shepherd, the Groenendael is an intense, alert, and highly versatile working dog used in police, military, and herding roles.

physical_traits.coat: Long, straight, abundant, all-black
physical_traits.tail: Moderately long, forming a slight curl at rest

health_considerations: Susceptible to hip and elbow dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, epilepsy, and cancer.
key_health_tips: Annual eye and joint evaluations. Extensive mental and physical exercise required daily to prevent behavioral issues in this high-drive breed.

description: The national dog of the Netherlands, the Keeshond is a lively, affectionate spitz with a spectacular gray-and-black double coat and distinctive spectacles markings around the eyes.

physical_traits.coat: Long, thick, harsh outer coat with dense undercoat, gray-black
physical_traits.tail: Tightly curled over back, double curl preferred

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, epilepsy, patent ductus arteriosus (PDA, a heart defect), hypothyroidism, and von Willebrand's disease.
key_health_tips: Annual cardiac and thyroid screenings. DNA test for vWD. Extensive double coat needs weekly brushing and biannual professional grooming.

description: Australia's premier working sheepdog, the Kelpie is an intensely energetic, intelligent herder capable of working livestock for hours in extreme heat.

physical_traits.ears: Pricked, slightly pointed, broad at base
physical_traits.coat: Short to medium, dense, double coat in black, chocolate, or tan

health_considerations: Generally very hardy. Prone to hip dysplasia and progressive retinal atrophy (PRA). Cerebellar abiotrophy has been identified in some bloodlines.
key_health_tips: DNA test for PRA and cerebellar abiotrophy where possible. Provide enormous amounts of daily activity — this breed needs a job to thrive.

description: A massive Hungarian flock guardian with a spectacular white corded coat that reaches the ground, the Komondor is fearless, calm, and fiercely protective.

physical_traits.coat: Long, white, naturally forming heavy cords
physical_traits.tail: Long, slightly curved, covered in cords

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, bloat, and skin problems that can develop under the cords. Regular coat maintenance is critical to prevent skin infections.
key_health_tips: Separate and dry cords thoroughly after bathing to prevent mildew and skin infections. Preventive gastropexy often recommended. Hip evaluations important.

description: A regal, white Hungarian flock guardian of ancient lineage, the Kuvasz is intelligent, protective, and devoted, with a dense white coat built for harsh winters.

physical_traits.ears: V-shaped, pendant, set at medium height
physical_traits.coat: Dense double coat, wavy or straight, white
physical_traits.tail: Low-set, long, carried low with slight upward curve

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, osteochondrosis, and bloat.
key_health_tips: OFA hip evaluations for breeding stock. Prevent bloat with structured feeding and meal timing. Early socialization is essential given the breed's guarding instincts.

description: One of the oldest and largest Arctic sled dogs, the Alaskan Malamute is a powerful, dignified working dog with wolf-like markings and a friendly, loyal personality.

physical_traits.coat: Thick double coat, coarse guard hairs, dense undercoat

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, inherited polyneuropathy, hypothyroidism, and hereditary cataracts.
key_health_tips: DNA test for polyneuropathy. Annual hip and eye evaluations. Heavy shedding twice yearly; regular brushing is essential to prevent coat matting.

description: The Belgian Malinois is a high-drive, world-class working dog used by military and police globally, known for its extreme intelligence, athleticism, and intensity.

physical_traits.coat: Short, straight, hard, fawn to mahogany with black mask

health_considerations: Prone to hip and elbow dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, epilepsy, and sensitivity to anesthesia in some bloodlines.
key_health_tips: Annual orthopedic and eye evaluations. Provide 2+ hours of intense exercise daily. Without structured activity and training, behavioral issues develop quickly.

description: Known as the 'King of Toys,' the Miniature Pinscher is a fearless, energetic dog with a distinctive high-stepping hackney gait, often mistaken for a miniature Doberman.

physical_traits.ears: Set high, erect when cropped or naturally button/drop
physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, close-lying, lustrous

health_considerations: Prone to patellar luxation, Legg-Calvé-Perthes, cardiac defects, and hypothyroidism.
key_health_tips: Annual orthopedic and cardiac evaluations. Protect from falls and jumping from heights. Use harness to protect trachea.

description: A highly intelligent, athletic, and elegant Poodle variety, the Miniature Poodle is a non-shedding companion with a proud bearing and joyful, playful nature.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, curly or corded, hypoallergenic-friendly
physical_traits.tail: Straight, set high, carried upright, traditionally docked

health_considerations: Prone to progressive retinal atrophy, epilepsy, Addison's disease, hip dysplasia, and Legg-Calvé-Perthes.
key_health_tips: Annual eye and orthopedic evaluations. Monitor adrenal function if lethargy or digestive issues appear. Regular professional grooming every 6-8 weeks.

description: The most popular of the three Schnauzer varieties, the Miniature Schnauzer is a sturdy, spirited terrier-like companion with a distinctive beard and eyebrows.

physical_traits.snout: Strong, blunt rectangular, with prominent beard
physical_traits.ears: V-shaped, erect when cropped, or folded forward
physical_traits.coat: Hard, wiry outer coat with close undercoat, salt-and-pepper, black, or silver

health_considerations: Prone to hyperlipidemia (high blood fats), pancreatitis, urinary stones, cataracts, and progressive retinal atrophy.
key_health_tips: Low-fat diet is critical; Miniature Schnauzers are highly prone to pancreatitis. Annual eye and lipid panel evaluations. Regular grooming every 6-8 weeks.

description: A rare, ancient English breed developed specifically to hunt otters on land and in water, the Otterhound is big, boisterous, and endearingly shaggy.

physical_traits.ears: Very long, pendant, low-set, folded inward
physical_traits.coat: Dense, rough, crisp double coat, water-resistant

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, thrombopathia (a blood clotting disorder), bloat, and ear infections.
key_health_tips: DNA test for thrombopathia in breeding dogs. Weekly ear cleaning is essential. Preventive gastropexy may be considered given deep-chest bloat risk.

description: Named for its butterfly-like fringed ears (papillon means 'butterfly' in French), this elegant and lively toy spaniel is one of the oldest and most athletic toy breeds.

physical_traits.ears: Large, butterfly-shaped, erect with long fringes
physical_traits.coat: Long, fine, silky, no undercoat

health_considerations: Prone to patellar luxation, dental overcrowding, hypoglycemia, and seizures. Progressive retinal atrophy occasionally noted.
key_health_tips: Regular dental cleanings due to overcrowding. Feed small frequent meals for hypoglycemia prevention. Annual orthopedic and eye evaluations.

description: With the motto 'multum in parvo' (much in little), the Pug is a charming, mischievous companion with a wrinkled face and curly tail that thrives on human attention.

physical_traits.ears: Small, thin, soft, rose or button shaped
physical_traits.coat: Fine, smooth, short, fawn or black
physical_traits.tail: Tightly curled over hip, double curl preferred

health_considerations: Significant brachycephalic obstructive airway syndrome (BOAS) issues. Also prone to Pug dog encephalitis (PDE), hip dysplasia, and eye injuries.
key_health_tips: BOAS evaluation and possible surgical correction. Clean facial wrinkles daily. Avoid heat exposure. Annual eye and neurological wellness checks.

description: A sleek, handsome American coonhound with a rich red coat, the Redbone is an enthusiastic night hunter with a melodious voice and an affectionate home personality.

physical_traits.coat: Short, dense, coarse, rich red

health_considerations: Generally healthy. Prone to hip dysplasia, ear infections from pendant ears, and obesity without adequate exercise.
key_health_tips: Weekly ear cleaning critical. Controlled diet to prevent weight gain. Provide outlets for scenting and tracking to satisfy natural instincts.

description: A small, fox-faced Belgian barge dog with a distinctive mane and a big personality, the Schipperke is curious, high-energy, and notorious for its mischief.

physical_traits.coat: Dense double coat with distinctive mane and culotte, black

health_considerations: Prone to Mucopolysaccharidosis type IIIB (MPS IIIB, a lysosomal storage disorder), hypothyroidism, and epilepsy.
key_health_tips: DNA test for MPS IIIB is available. Annual thyroid evaluations. Provide mental stimulation and secure containment; this breed is an expert escape artist.

description: An Australian toy terrier with a luxuriously silky, blue and tan coat, the Silky Terrier is feisty, alert, and surprisingly tough for its diminutive size.

physical_traits.coat: Fine, silky, parted on back, blue and tan

health_considerations: Prone to Legg-Calvé-Perthes, patellar luxation, intervertebral disc disease, and tracheal collapse.
key_health_tips: Use harness not collar to protect trachea. Minimize high jumping. Annual orthopedic evaluations. Daily brushing prevents coat matting.

description: A joyful, exuberant Irish farm dog, the Soft-Coated Wheaten Terrier sports a silky wheaten coat and a greeting style known as the 'Wheaten hello' involving jumping and licking.

physical_traits.coat: Soft, silky, gently waving, wheaten color

health_considerations: Prone to protein-losing nephropathy (PLN), protein-losing enteropathy (PLE), hip dysplasia, and Addison's disease.
key_health_tips: Urine and blood protein checks annually due to PLN and PLE risk. Low-protein diet may be required. Annual adrenal and orthopedic evaluations.

description: Far more than a pampered show dog, the Standard Poodle is an athletic, intelligent, and versatile breed, widely considered one of the smartest dogs in the world.

physical_traits.snout: Long, straight, fine, chiseled below the eyes
physical_traits.ears: Wide, thick, pendant, close to head
physical_traits.coat: Dense, curly or corded, can be styled
physical_traits.tail: Straight, set high, carried upright, traditionally docked

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, progressive retinal atrophy, Addison's disease, bloat, and sebaceous adenitis (a skin condition).
key_health_tips: Annual eye and adrenal evaluations. Feed structured meals to prevent bloat. Skin evaluations for sebaceous adenitis annually. Regular professional grooming required.

description: The original and middle-sized Schnauzer, the Standard Schnauzer is a versatile, robust working dog from Germany with a distinguished appearance and spirited personality.

physical_traits.ears: V-shaped, set high, erect when cropped or folded
physical_traits.coat: Harsh, wiry outer coat with close undercoat, pepper-and-salt or black

health_considerations: Generally healthy. Prone to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, and follicular dermatitis.
key_health_tips: Annual thyroid checks and OFA hip evaluations. Coat requires professional hand-stripping every 3-4 months to maintain texture.

description: The smallest of the Poodle varieties, the Toy Poodle carries the same extraordinary intelligence and athletic ability in a compact, elegant, and charming package.

physical_traits.coat: Dense, curly, non-shedding
physical_traits.tail: Straight, set high, docked or natural

health_considerations: Prone to patellar luxation, progressive retinal atrophy, Legg-Calvé-Perthes, hypoglycemia, and tracheal collapse.
key_health_tips: Frequent small meals to prevent hypoglycemia. Use harness to protect trachea. Annual orthopedic and eye evaluations. Professional grooming every 6-8 weeks.

description: The English Toy Terrier is a sleek, elegant miniaturized hunting terrier, historically used to kill rats in sporting events, now an affectionate and alert companion.

physical_traits.ears: Large, erect, candle-flame shaped, set high
physical_traits.coat: Thick, close, glossy, black and tan
physical_traits.tail: Short, thick at base, tapers to a point

health_considerations: Prone to patellar luxation, Legg-Calvé-Perthes, heat sensitivity, and dental crowding.
key_health_tips: Protect from extreme cold; this breed has very little body fat. Orthopedic evaluations annually. Regular dental checks for crowding issues.

description: Hungary's golden-rust pointer, the Vizsla is a sensitive, gentle, and highly affectionate sporting breed that bonds deeply with its family and craves constant companionship.

physical_traits.coat: Short, smooth, dense, golden-rust
physical_traits.tail: Docked to 2/3 length or natural, carried horizontal

health_considerations: Prone to hip dysplasia, hypothyroidism, progressive retinal atrophy, epilepsy, and various cancers.
key_health_tips: Annual thyroid and eye evaluations. OFA hip screening. Provide vigorous daily exercise; Vizslas develop anxiety without adequate activity and human companionship.

description: The 'Poor Man's Racehorse,' the Whippet is a gentle, affectionate sighthound that can reach 35 mph, equally at home sprinting on a track and napping on the sofa.

physical_traits.coat: Short, close, smooth
physical_traits.tail: Long, tapering, carried low with slight upward curve

health_considerations: Generally healthy and long-lived. Sensitive to anesthesia as a sighthound. Prone to heart murmurs, eye issues, and skin injuries due to thin skin.
key_health_tips: Inform vet of sighthound anesthesia sensitivity. Protect from cold with a coat in winter. Annual cardiac and eye evaluations. Secure fencing is essential.

description: A classic British terrier with a bold, outgoing personality and a distinctive broken-textured white and colored coat, the Wire Fox Terrier is energetic, fearless, and fun.

physical_traits.ears: Small, V-shaped, folded forward, dropping close to cheek
physical_traits.coat: Dense, wiry, twisted, with soft undercoat

health_considerations: Prone to Legg-Calvé-Perthes, lens luxation, deafness, and patellar luxation.
key_health_tips: Annual eye and orthopedic evaluations. BAER hearing test in puppies. Hand-strip the coat rather than clip to maintain proper texture and water resistance.
